title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Nov 3 2022
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Nov 3 2022
description:
Biden speech: The oration from Union Station that was a desecration. Buck says, "I think they're keeping the democracy in peril theme in place in order to run against Trump." In an alarming tone, even bringing your kids into it, historian Michael Beschloss says midterms will determine the future of democracy. Undergrad history major Clay, who says he considered getting a PhD in the subject, says, "Buck and I are both history nerds... I went to Civil War sleepover camp. I am a legitimate Civil War nerd." Biden: You can't love your country only when you win. That's why there was lots of Democrat denial after the 2016 election. Another woman brutally raped in Kathy Hochul's New York. Bo Hines, GOP candidate in North Carolina's 13th Congressional District, joins Clay and Buck for an energized talk.

Follow Clay & Buck on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/c/clayandbuck
